      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your loan interest is calculated on your remaining principal balance each month, which is how the balance seems to move slowly at first. A significant portion of your initial payments goes toward covering the accrued interest before much actually reduces the principal. It's like a cycle where the interest keeps building on the remaining debt, making the principal reduction feel slow when you're just starting out. You might consider paying extra toward the principal to speed up the process.",
