      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can use an amortization calculator, which plugs in your loan details and payment amounts to show you the payoff timeline. This tool will clearly illustrate the difference between minimum payments and those with extra principal payments. Adding even a small extra amount, like $50 or $100, can significantly shorten the loan term over time. It's a powerful way to visualize how that extra cash directly attacks the principal, rather than just feeding the interest.",
